parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Wiring Short Circuit
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a fire in the trunk, leading to a risk of vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities. The sudden loss of power can also cause the vehicle to shut off in the middle of the road, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the trunk
vehicle shutting off in the middle of the road
burning smell
electrical system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Driver-Side Airbag to Deploy in Frontal Collision
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver-side airbag to deploy in a frontal collision can increase the risk of serious injury or death to the driver, as the airbag is designed to provide critical protection in such situations.
symptoms: The driver-side airbag does not deploy in a frontal collision
despite the vehicle's speed and impact severity meeting the deployment criteria.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accident, or injury to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment
burning smell or odor
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard
loss of engine power
unusual engine noise or sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty fuel system components can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to engine compartment fires, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor
fuel leaks
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling
decreased engine performance
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause engine compartment fires, accidents, or injuries due to faulty wiring, connectors, or components.
symptoms: Warning lights or alarms on the dashboard
burning smell or odor
unusual electrical noises or sounds
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
often when shifting into gear or when the vehicle is stationary
and may continue to accelerate even when the driver attempts to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty transmission control module can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
often when shifting into gear or when the vehicle is stationary
and may continue to accelerate even when the driver attempts to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake-throttle override system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
often when shifting into gear or when the vehicle is stationary
and may continue to accelerate even when the driver attempts to brake.
